{"/service/ndnp/ak/batch_ak_harborseal_ver04/data/2017218598/00279525784/1914022101/0378.xml":{"full_text":"The work of decorating Brown\nHawkins hall for the big party tonight\nhas been completed, and the big bail\nroom is a bower of beauty. The dance\nbids fair to surpass anything of its\nkind that has ever been held in Seward\nand promises to usher in the dawn of\nthe long waited for prosperity in a\nmanner fitting to the occasion and\nworthy of the two business houses wiio\nare combining tonight to entertain the\nresidents of the Kenai peninsula.\nArrangements have been made to\ndntertain the largest crowd in the\nhistory of Seward and not one thing\nhas been left undone that could possibly\nadd to the pleasure or enjoyment of\nthe guests, even to providing dainty\nand appropriate souvenirs of the oc\ncasion, that will be presented to all\nwho attend. Dancing will begin at 9\np. m.\nFrank J. Cotter and Sidney Ander\nson, both drawn for jury duty at Cor\ndova for the March term of court, have\nbeen excused from attendance by\nJudge Brown. I\nMrs. Charles Krefting and daughter\nElinore Marion are doing nicely ac\ncording to Dr. Baughman, and will\nsoon be out to take advantage of the\nearly spring weather that Sewardites\nare enjoying.\nLong distance telephone booth at the\nBranch.\nField glasses at J. L. Graef\u2019s.\nIce creepers and ice skates at J. L.\nGraefs.\nSnow Glasses Snow Glasses Snow\nGlasses. 50c with case up to $5.00.\nGeorge the Jeweler.\nThe Alaska House is on the market.\nSee George the Jeweler.\nII\nMeet meat the branch.\n_ m\na man lilies a woman that s his business.\nA nd if a woman libes a man\u2014that\u2019s her busi\nness.\ny^nd if they get mairied\u2014that's their business.\nRUT-CLEANING. PRESSINC\nD AND tailoring\nMY BUSINESS.\n~c7henning\nAgent for\nFRED KAUFFMA\u2019NN CLOTHES\nKDFFTiP CARPtNTtR\nllWsi \u00a71! BUILDER\nBlue Ribbon Beer\nOlympia Beer\nJ. P. Stotko Proprietor\nThe Garstens Packing Go.\nJust arrived on the Northwestern\nfresh supply of\nBeef, Pork, Veal, Mutton, Broil\ners, Roasting Chickens, Fowls,\nButter, Eggs, Etc.\nPRICES CUT AS USUAL.\nC. A. Myers, Manager\n5 ir-lf jfmjjjf V\" BTJ fjjr j\u00bb jJH l\u00a3qfeJa jffi *tF F ff\nE believe in our country\u2014Tlie United\nStates of America\u2014and the princi\nples for which she stands. We believe\nSeward lias passed thru what is termed\n\u201ctimes of business depression\u201d but the\nperiod was for preparation for greater and\nmore pronounced commercial successes.\nWe believe that the passage of the Alaska\nRailroad bill means that Seward will be\nthe metropolis of Alaska. We believe\nthat Resurrection bay has the best anchor\nage and is the best harbor in Alaska.\nJointly with Brown Hawkins we\nextend to you a cordial invitation to be\nour guest at a dance to be given in Brown\nHawkins\u2019 hall, Saturday night, Febru\nary 21st.\nH. V. HOBEN A. F. DAVIS\nSA \\A \\NSFER\nH. V. HOBEN, Manager\n-\u2014\u2014Dealers in--\u2014--\u2014\n\nGeneral Transferring Phones, Main 17 and 41\nt i\n5l _ Ji _ lI \u00a3.E .l.4 i u ^jj3\nEVERYONE\nWELCOME\nGood Music\nand a Grand\nTime Assured\nto Everyone\na-\nIf you don\u2019t\ncare to dance,\ncome and en\njoy your fill of\nCake, Ice\nCream,Candy,\nHot Coffee\nand Sand\nwiches.\nI\n\n\u2022J t I J-.J. f f i vrv 1, s..; i*\ni<: r","height":"38610","width":"23601"}}
